# Task Management

## Follow Task List Strictly

- Complete tasks exactly as specified in task list
- Don't over-implement or add extra features
- Don't add structure before it's needed

## One Task at a Time

- Focus on the current task only
- Don't anticipate future needs with extra scaffolding
- Move to next task only when current is complete

## Renaming Exported Symbols

When renaming any exported symbol (function, variable, type, config):

- Grep the full codebase for all usages before declaring done
- Respect `.cursorignore` — exclude any files and folders listed there
- Use: `rg "oldName" --type ts`

## Examples Over Premature Abstraction

- Don't use the project to illustrate examples
- Ask clarifying questions for future planning without implementing
- Keep it simple until complexity is actually needed

## Task File Conventions

Task files live in `tasks/` at the repo root — one file per initiative (e.g., `tasks/google-ads-launch.md`).

**Format:** Phase sections → named tasks → checkbox action items:

```markdown
## Phase 1 — Phase Name

Brief description of why this phase matters.

### Task 1.1: Task name

- [ ] Action item
- [ ] Action item

### Task 1.2: Task name

- [ ] Action item
```

- Never nest `- [ ]` items — flat list only, hierarchy implied by `Task N.N` numbering
- Nested markdown lists render inconsistently across editors
